					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>The revised recension of Maimonides' Sefer mitsṿot in the original Arabic, in Hebrew characters. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="">Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="168v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Sefer mitsṿot </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר מצות</title>
							<note>
								<p>Folios 1-10r contain a fragmentary enumeration of the 613 precepts in the actual wording of the Pentateuch (cf Or. 1046, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">504</ref>), thus differing from the enumeration in Moses ibn Tibbon's Hebrew translation, where a free wording is adopted. </p>
								<p>Introduction begins on folio 10r, Mitsvot ʿaseh on folio 36r, and Mitsṿot lo taʿaseh on folio 89r. </p>
								<p>Folio 164r is a duplicate of folio 162r due to a mistake of the scribe. </p>
								<p>References from most mitsṿot to Maimonides' Mishneh Torah have been added on the margin. </p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="en">Maimonides, Moses, 1135-1204 </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="he">משה בן מימון, 1138-1204 </persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th to 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>168 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>220</height>
										<width>160</width>
									</dimensions>
